INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_2035_L026$$, 2026, $$C2 Transport funding supports the Army's Next Generation Command and Control (NGC2) initiative to modernize Command and Control (C2) systems, Transport Layer across Tactical Networks, Multi-
 Mission Radios and Satellite Terminals. C2 Transport enables the capability to move and synchronize data; and is focused on delivering a lean, flat, Global Mesh Architecture which is Data-Centric, AI-driven,
 software defined, quantum resistant and Disconnected, Denied, Intermittent, and/or Limited Bandwidth (DDIL) survivable. NGC2 architecture requires diverse and layered transport that maximizes the full
 range of available spectrum and provides options for a unit's signature profile while maintaining data connectivity. C2 Transport FY27 plan is to continue procurement for the C2 Now 30-month replacement and
 divestment of legacy WIN-T as well as procuring 3 NGC2 divisions/equivalents of the Transport layer which includes the Satellite Terminals (LEO/GEO), Software Defined Networking, Line of Sight (LOS) and
 Multi Mission Radio efforts.

 C2 Transport (B11500) is established in FY2027 as part of a new funding structure for the Next Generation Command and Control (NGC2) investment in modernization of Army Command and Control (C2)
 Systems. A funding line consolidation and structure change for the NGC2 investment provides clarity and transparency for the NGC2 four layered approach (Applications, Data, Transport, and Infrastructure). C2
 Transport B11500 is not a new start line, it is a consolidation of Tactical Network Communications (B11200), Air Ground Networking Radio (B95017), COTS Communications Equipment (BU8100) and Satellite
 Communications (B56000).

 Tactical Networks (B11511) enables the procurement of Command Control Network Optimized for Warfighting - Transport (C2NOW-T), Tactical C2 Transport, and Fixed/Rapidly Deployable C2 Transport.
 Tactical Network funds enable mission command capabilities and connect highly mobile and dispersed forces together, procuring a portfolio of products that deliver the latest Commercial-Off-the-Shelf (COTS)
 networking and communications capabilities to enable the Warfighter's ability to conduct Mission Command at every stage of operations - from home station to early entry to the most austere environments of the
 battlefield. These capabilities augment, extend, and strengthen the tactical network by providing rapidly deployable, high-throughput, low-latency Line-of-Sight (LOS) and Beyond Line-of-Sight (BLOS) capabilities
 and cutting-edge networking systems, providing network connectivity and transport for the ground domain to connect with the Department of Defense Information Network (DoDIN). These capabilities modernize
 equipment previously procured under Tactical Network Communications (B11200 - B11225/B11226).

 Multi-Mission Radios (B11512) enables the procurement of Multi-Mission Transport. Multi-Mission Radios procure COTS, non-developmental items (NDI), or sister Service developed solutions and services
 providing interoperability and continuity through the procurement of tactical communication enhancement equipment, ancillaries, and related services. These items provide resilient software-defined
 communication systems and operational utility and adaptability through simplified and protected communications for soldier-borne, ground maneuver and air maneuver communications. This line modernizes
 equipment previously procured under Air Ground Networking Radio (B95017), Low-Cost Tactical Radio Replacement (LCTTR, B08105), High Frequency Radios (B98120), Small Unit and Emergency Locator
 Communications (B98121).$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Army                                                                                                                      Date: April 2026
