INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_2035_L113$$, 2026, $$C2 Infrastructure (B11400) is established in FY2027 as part of a new funding structure for the Next Generation Command and Control (NGC2) investment in modernization of Army Command and Control (C2)
 Systems. A funding line consolidation and structure change for the NGC2 investment provides clarity and transparency for the NGC2 four layered approach (Applications, Data, Transport, and Infrastructure).

 This C2 Infrastructure PE supports NGC2 efforts under the Infrastructure Layer and does not constitute a new program or effort. Funding for the NGC2 Infrastructure Layer activities was provided in FY2026
 under Army Command Post Integrated Infrastructure (B29810), Data Products (BA9315), Joint Battle Command Platform (W61990), UNIFIED NETWORK OPERATIONS (UNO) / (B99418), Networked Radios
 Planner (B98112), and Cross Domain Solutions (B98113).

 B11400 represents a strategic investment to modernize the Army's C2 systems, enhancing operational effectiveness and resilience on the battlefield. C2 Infrastructure supports NGC2 infrastructure layer
 activities and the Command and Control Network Optimized for Warfighting (C2NOW) Infrastructure acceleration efforts. C2NOW is a 30 month acceleration effort, providing a down payment on NGC2, initiating
 in 4QFY26 to divest of legacy tactical server infrastructure hardware and replace with NGC2 capable hardware. The C2 Infrastructure transforms the Army's command and control capabilities by providing a
 cohesive and integrated infrastructure that enables real-time communication and coordination across all levels of operations. This initiative is essential for ensuring the Army can effectively respond to evolving
 threats and maintain operational flexibility in contested environments.

 The C2 Infrastructure (B11400) funding line is the parent line of C2 Compute Infrastructure (B11411), Mounted C2 Infrastructure (B11412), and C2 Infrastructure Components (B11413).

 B11411, C2 Compute Infrastructure, supports integration efforts to establish resilient command posts that adapt to evolving operational needs. This infrastructure provides a modular, distributable solution for
 hosting NGC2 applications, simplifying upgrades and addressing integration challenges through open standards. It facilitates the incorporation of multiple NGC2 enabling technologies across various vehicle
 platforms, supporting an open architecture and a data-centric design that ensures interoperability and ease of integration across diverse networks. Additionally, it enhances scalability and network resiliency,
 allowing tactical units to communicate effectively in hostile environments. C2 Compute Infrastructure supports the Army Computing Infrastructure (ACI) project by modernizing the Army Edge Computing
 Capability (AECC), Army's compute and store, supporting Joint and NGC2 initiatives. This funding supports both NGC2 and C2NOW mission.

 B11412, Mounted C2 Infrastructure, delivers on-the-move high bandwidth necessary to meet the expanded mounted infrastructure demands of the NGC2 warfighting applications. Army will use a modular
 open systems approach to maximize flexibility through rapid technology insertion and non-proprietary technologies to provide significantly higher data transfer rates and communications resiliency over legacy$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Army                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
