 threats and maintain operational flexibility in contested environments.

 The C2 Infrastructure (B11400) funding line is the parent line of C2 Compute Infrastructure (B11411), Mounted C2 Infrastructure (B11412), and C2 Infrastructure Components (B11413).

 B11411, C2 Compute Infrastructure, supports integration efforts to establish resilient command posts that adapt to evolving operational needs. This infrastructure provides a modular, distributable solution for
 hosting NGC2 applications, simplifying upgrades and addressing integration challenges through open standards. It facilitates the incorporation of multiple NGC2 enabling technologies across various vehicle
 platforms, supporting an open architecture and a data-centric design that ensures interoperability and ease of integration across diverse networks. Additionally, it enhances scalability and network resiliency,
 allowing tactical units to communicate effectively in hostile environments. C2 Compute Infrastructure supports the Army Computing Infrastructure (ACI) project by modernizing the Army Edge Computing
 Capability (AECC), Army's compute and store, supporting Joint and NGC2 initiatives. This funding supports both NGC2 and C2NOW mission.

 B11412, Mounted C2 Infrastructure, delivers on-the-move high bandwidth necessary to meet the expanded mounted infrastructure demands of the NGC2 warfighting applications. Army will use a modular
 open systems approach to maximize flexibility through rapid technology insertion and non-proprietary technologies to provide significantly higher data transfer rates and communications resiliency over legacy



