INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3010_L008$$, 2027, $$Collaborative Combat Aircraft (CCA) are uncrewed weapon systems capable of enhancing crewed weapon systems ability to achieve air superiority. Key CCA capabilities include mission-integrated autonomy,
 multi-platform interoperability, and collaborative lethality enhancement with those interoperable platforms. CCA will contribute to multiple mission requirements and provide Combatant Commanders (CCDR) with
 options for enhancing manned-platform capability in Highly Contested Environments (HCE).

 The FY27 budget request initiates the procurement of Collaborative Combat Aircraft (CCA), an uncrewed system. This funding will support the procurement of the initial air vehicles, ground control systems,
 and the integration of mission systems and autonomy packages. Specifically, funds will be allocated to air vehicle production, government-furnished equipment (GFE), and program management to ensure the
 establishment of a robust production line and to support initial operational testing and evaluation activities.

 CCA will procure air vehicle prime mission equipment (PME) and alternate mission equipment (AME) based on operational requirements, threat evolution, and/or technological opportunities. PME and AME
 opportunities may include, but are not limited to, communication, electronic warfare, radio frequency, and infrared mission systems.

 This requirement supports performance of a full financial audit as required by title 10 U.S.C. Chapter 9A, Sec 240-D.

 In accordance with Section 1815 of the FY2008 National Defense Authorization Act (P.L. 110-181), this item is necessary for use by the active components of the Armed Forces for homeland defense missions,
 domestic emergency responses, and providing military support to civil authorities.

 Funding may be used to address Diminishing Manufacturing Sources (DMS) issues.

 Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0207147F.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Air Force                                                                                                                Date: April 2026
