INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3010_L013_v23$$, 2027, $$The Advanced Pilot Training (APT)/ T-7A Red Hawk program will replace the Air Education Training Commands (AETC) aging T-38C fleet with new aircraft, Ground Based Training Systems (simulators, training
 devices, computer based training systems, academics, etc.), Maintenance Training Systems, and support infrastructure currently used in the Advanced Fighter/Bomber Fundamentals Course.

 The APT/T-7A Red Hawk program acquisition strategy was approved by OUSW (A&S) in early FY 2017 (December 2016). The Program completed source selection evaluations and Milestone B in September
 2018 and awarded a Fixed Price Incentive Firm Indefinite Delivery /Indefinite Quantity contract to The Boeing Company on 27 September 2018. Critical Design Review was completed in August 2020. An updated
 acquisition strategy was approved by the Air Force Senior Acquisition Authority in February 2026 approving a strategy to persue Advance Procurement beginning in FY27. Milestone C is currently projected for
 3Q FY 2026 with the first Low-Rate Initial Production deliveries anticipated in 3Q FY 2027.

 Funding Contained in this platform's documentation directly aids AETC flying training enterprise to continue its overall pilot production increase to reduce the USAF Pilot Shortage. This requirement supports
 performance of a full financial audit as required by title 10 U.S.C. Chapter 9A, Sec 240-D.

 Funding may be used to address Diminishing Manufacturing Sources/Material Shortage (DMSMS) issues.

 Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0804701F.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Air Force                                                                                                                Date: April 2026
