 Description:
 The EDS-II replacement program is a comprehensive permanent sustainment modification designed to replace the obsolete auxiliary maintenance computer, the no longer procurable Personal Computer
 Interface Unit, and key loading panel with a modern computing architecture and permanent ancillary equipment. The modification will simplify the design, enable ethernet loading of mission software, allow for
 back up radio cryptographic key loading, combat obsolete data transfer medium, and drive non-mission capable rates down by 900+ hours per year. Without this modification, aircraft project to be grounded
 starting in FY 2029.

 This program integrates, procures and installs production ready kits to modify the C-5 aircraft.

 Due to Diminishing Manufacturing Sources (DMS) and parts obsolescence issues with the current EDS, the solution development, design review, and prototype flight test are being accomplished with Weapon
 System Sustainment (WSS) sustaining engineering funds.

 Milestone/Development Status

 The development effort for EDS-II is part of ongoing efforts to resolve DMS and obsolescence issues with the current EDS installed on the C-5 aircraft. Due to Diminishing Manufacturing Sources (DMS) and
 parts obsolescence issues with the current EDS, the solution development, design review, and prototype flight test are being accomplished with Weapon System Sustainment (WSS) sustaining engineering
 funds.
