INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3010_L009_v23$$, 2027, $$Collaborative Combat Aircraft (CCA) are uncrewed weapon systems capable of enhancing crewed weapon systems ability to achieve air superiority. Key CCA capabilities include mission-integrated autonomy,
 multi-platform interoperability, and collaborative lethality enhancement with those interoperable platforms.

 The FY27 request for CCA includes 150,500 thousands of Advanced Procurement.

 The FY27 budget request initiates the procurement of Collaborative Combat Aircraft (CCA), an uncrewed system. This funding will support the procurement of the initial air vehicles, ground control systems,
 and the integration of mission systems and autonomy packages. Specifically, funds will be allocated to air vehicle production, government-furnished equipment (GFE), and program management to ensure the
 establishment of a robust production line and to support initial operational testing and evaluation activities.

 Funding includes aircraft flyaway costs, producibility improvement/incentives towards the active management strategy, support equipment, alternate mission equipment, training, spares, depot standup,
 engineering change orders and other government costs, such as program support costs. Funding may also be used to resolve Diminishing Manufacturing Sources and Material Shortages (DMSMS) and/or
 obsolescence issues. DMSMS activities may include, but are not limited to, bridge buys, life of type buys, buys to protect production schedule, and minor engineering efforts.

 This program is reported in accordance with Title 10, United States Code, Section 119(a)(1) in the Special Access Program Annual Report to Congress. For further information, please contact the Director of
 Special Programs, OUSD(A&AS)/DSP.

 Funding for this exhibit is contained in PE 0207147F.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Advance Procurement Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Air Force                                                                            Date: April 2026
