INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3010_L045$$, 2027, $$Modular Mission Computer (MMC) and Program Display Generator (PDG) Upgrade is a modification which upgrades the F-16 core mission computer to include increased high-speed data throughput, additional
 memory, and an Ethernet High Speed Data Network (HSDN) to realize full Active Electronically Scanned Array (AESA) radar capabilities. HSDN includes Ethernet Switch Upgrade (ESU). This modification
 incorporates the installation of Remote Interface Panels (RIP), which allows for the transfer of mission planning loaded data. The upgraded Programmable Display Generator (PDG) allows for a fully integrated
 Multi-Function Display Set (MFDS) solution including Hands-on Throttle and Stick (HOTAS) integration with Sensor of Interest (SOI), format swapping and high-definition video on 4x4 displays. The upgraded
 PDG also provides improved display formats during dynamic maneuvers; resolves symbol freezing issues due to throughput constraints; adds advanced processing cards and provides a sustainable approach to
 address growing DMS concerns with the current PDG. Minor NRE for Advanced Processing is listed under Group A NRE.

 Combined MMC/PDG/HSDN/RIP+ Group A kit installs are performed at the depot level, reflected in Mod Item 1 (to build install schedule). Individual costs of Group A and B buys listed under remaining Mod
 Items. MMC & PDG Group B kit installs occur at the field level at no cost. MMC kit Group B installs started in Oct 24 at 13 per month. PDG kit Group B installs expected to start in Apr 27 at 13 per month.

 The original quantity of 608 was reduced to 603 installs for MMC and 603 installs for PDG. HSDN & RIP+ required on 186 a/c under this program (remainder of Post-Blk fleet under AESA program). Advanced
 Processing Cards total 1206 (2 per a/c). ESU is 179 a/c under this program (remainder of Post-Blk fleet under AESA program).

 This funding request will support potential DMS and obsolescence solutions, to include, if optimal, life of type buys, or bridge buys limited to the program of record quantity.

 Milestone/Development Status

 MMC - Milestone C achieved Mar 23
 PDG - Complete two TVIs and two kit-proofs (one TVI/KP for 3-Line Ethernet Harness Jul 25 & one TVI/KP for DVI Harness Aug 25). DT June 23 (w/ install at Edwards on jet 0383), OT Jan 24 (w/ install at Eglin
 at jet 0497), IOT&E Apr 24. PDG Milestone C (fielding recommendation) slipped to Apr 27 (tied to OFP M8.2 fielding, M8.2 fielding delayed to Apr 27).$$, $$$$, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Air Force                                                                                                                         Date: April 2026
