 Description:
 This program, P-3A Mod 6140, C-32 SAT-906, is a new start.
 The program requirement is to replace the SAT 906 satellite communications system with the Cobham AVIATOR INMARSAT system on C-32A aircraft. The SAT 906 system is approaching obsolescence.
 Starting in FY24, spares available has decreased and the system will become unrepairable. The new AVIATOR INMARSAT system on the C-32A will provide aircrews the capability to communicate with Air
 Traffic Control (ATC) and will provide C-32A passengers several backup communication lines in order to conduct business while airborne. This installation satisfies C-32A Future Air Navigation System (FANS)
 and Aircraft Communication Addressing and Reporting System (ACARS) certifications for direct communications between aircrew and air traffic controllers regarding clearances, pilot requests, and position
 reporting while airborne.

 Loss of FANS or ACARS certification will greatly impact mission capability by causing C-32A to plan/fly non-optimal routes and altitudes, potentially increasing flight distance and time while decreasing fuel
 efficiency. Loss of FANS or ACARS certification will also increase pilot workload by requiring more frequent position reporting to ATC, potentially leading to errors and increased safety risk.

 The source of this requirement is contained in AMC AF 1067 17-023.

 This funding may include, but is not limited to, emerging modification requirements to support Program Support Costs (PSC), system integration lab, trainers, equipment, and other government costs (OGC).

 FY 2027 efforts will include non-recurring engineering and installation contract actions for the first-of-model aircraft to award beginning in 4QFY27.

 This modification is subject to aircraft availability. This is in alignment with required lead times for nonrecurring engineering for installation and scheduled C 32-A depot inductions.

 This modification supports performance of a full financial audit as required by title 10 U.S.C. Chapter 9A, Sec 240-D.

 Milestone/Development Status

 C-32A SAT-906 integration to begin in 4QFY27.




