INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3010_L058$$, 2027, $$The T-6 is a single-engine advance trainer aircraft. The T-6 aircraft is used by Air Education and Training Command (AETC) as an entry-level trainer for joint primary pilot training, teaching basic flying skills.
 The T-6 aircraft provides significant improvements over the aircraft it replaced, including a 0/0 ejection seat which accommodates a larger anthropometric pilot population, a pressurized cockpit, gravitational-force
 (g-force) strain reduction capabilities, and increased bird strike protection. There are currently 442 USAF T-6A aircraft [441 AETC A/C; one (1) USAF Owned, OEM Test A/C] in the inventory. Remaining service
 life is through Dec 2049.

 Funding contained in this platform's documentation directly aids Air Education Training Command (AETC) flying training enterprise to continue its overall pilot production increase thus reducing the USAF Pilot
 Shortage.

 Funding will support modification efforts related but not limited to the Avionics Replacement Program (ARP), modification recovery efforts, Service Bulletins, and Low Cost Modifications. Funding may be used to
 address Diminishing Manufacturing Sources (DMS) issues

 These modifications support performance of a full financial audit as required by title 10 U.S.C. Chapter 9A, Sec 240-D

